Browser Fingerprinting and Web Activity Tracking -
We have to explore the boundary of control between User and System.
Who should own the User Interface?
How do we ensure that the code which produces our interfaces can be trusted?

Unstructured Information - I've read somewhere that 94% of the information in the world is unstructured.
I've also read that the amount of unstructured information is increasing much faster than structured.
I have no doubt we are in the digital dark ages.

Why is "scraping the web" different than "using the web"?
There should be no distinction,
the web should seamlessly bridge the gap between man and machine.

